The paper deals with achieving strong secrecy over wiretap channels, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed solutions involve source-channel coding architectures, which are also relevant to coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of randomness and compression, which are topics in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
